                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverioTacc"/>, <citedRange>VIII</citedRange> (no image)</bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>152a</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>006100</citedRange></bibl>. 
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#maffre2007"/>, p. 171, n. <citedRange>20</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><w lemma="δεκάτα">δεκάταν</w> <persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="Ἀπόλλων">τὀ<supplied reason="lost">πόλōνι</supplied></name></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Untel a consacré</supplied> comme dîme à Apollon.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">So-and-so dedicated</supplied> as a tithe to Apollo.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Il tale ha dedicato</supplied> come decima ad Apollo.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Published from a drawing in Oliverio's papers, without description nor illustration. The date is only conjectural.</p>
                <p>The reference to 'Tacc(uino) VIII' indicates excavations of 1927.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
